A circle is inscribed in a square with perimeter of 32 inches. What is the circumference of the circle, in inches? Express your answer in terms of $\pi$.
}

\textbf{Answer:} The length of the diameter of the circle is equal to the square's side length. The side length of the square is $(32\text{ in.})/4=8$ inches. Therefore, the circumference of the circle is $\pi\cdot(8\text{ in.})=\boxed{8\pi}$ inches.
